sentences: František Neumann was born in Přerov, Moravia in 1874.

His serious music studies commenced in 1896 at the Leipzig Conservatory under Carl Reinecke and Salomon Jadassohn, and continued under Felix Mottl in Karlsruhe, where he worked as chorus master at the local theatre.
Further posts were at Hamburg, Ratisbon, Linz, Liberec, Teplice and Frankfurt, where he remained until 1919.
He returned to Czechoslovakia and became Chief Conductor at the National Theatre in Brno, becoming its director in 1925.

sentences: František Neumann (16 June 1874 – 25 February 1929) was a Czech conductor and composer.
He spent a year in voluntary military service at Olomouc, then joined his father's smoked meat business.
In his first season 1919-20 he introduced regular subscription concerts, and he brought a much needed discipline to the fledgling organisation.
